<h1><b>Codeterpret</b></h1>
<p>Codeterpret is an open source web based tool that allows developers to create and translate database schemas, as well and generate corresponding back-end APIs and front-end code, in effort to help take the monotony out of setting up the foundation of a new application. The end goal is to produce output for many databases, back-end languages, and front-end frameworks, but for now, in phase one development, my focus is  <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/sql-server/sql-server-2019" target="_blank">SQL Server</a>/<a href="https://www.mysql.com/" target="_blank">MySQL</a>, <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/csharp/" target="_blank">C#</a> <a href="https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download" target="_blank">.NET Core</a> 3.1+, <a href="https://angular.io/" target="_blank">Angular</a> 10+</p>

<p>The code behind this application is <a href="https://dotnet.microsoft.com/apps/aspnet/web-apps/blazor" target="_blank">Blazor</a>, <a href="https://blazorise.com/" target="_blank">Blazorise</a>, <a href="https://codemirror.net/" target="_blank">CodeMirror</a></p>
